1) Create the empty folder
2) cretae index.js
3) run "npm init" to initialized the "package.json" file
4) Install Express package by using this command "npm install express --save" 
5) Insatall "Nodemon" globally using --> "npm i -g nodemon" 
6) Can Install Angular/Cli using "npm uninstall package_name"

/* 
     Also can uninstall any package using "npm uninstall package_name" 
*/


////////////////////////////////////////////
Express
------------------------

Express.js, or simply Express, is a back end web application framework for building RESTful APIs with Node.js


Nodemon
---------------------------------------

A command-line tool that helps with the speedy development of Node. js applications. 
It monitors your project directory and automatically restarts your node application when it detects any 
changes. This means that you do not have to stop and restart your applications in order for your changes to 
take effect.

